# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Classyx — client-side Supabase config
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Copy this file to ".env"      ->   cp .env.example .env
# 2. Fill in the values from your Supabase project:
#       Supabase Dashboard -> Project Settings -> Data API  (URL)
#       Supabase Dashboard -> Project Settings -> API Keys  (anon / publishable key)
#
# These two values are PUBLIC by design. They ship in the browser bundle and
# that is expected — your data is protected by Row Level Security (RLS), not by
# hiding the key. See README.md ("Security model").
#
# !!  NEVER put the service_role (secret) key in this file, in .env, or in any
# !!  front-end code. It bypasses RLS and would expose your entire database.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-public-anon-key-here
VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=0x4AAAAAADpSfVDp1j7V2mzn